--- Employee Tree ---
Web app that displays the employee hierarchy in tree form.

The tree was based on a snippet https://bootsnipp.com/snippets/orp8g

http://127.0.0.1:8000/ - simple tree
http://127.0.0.1:8000/employee_tree_with_changing_bosses - tree with the ability to change the boss by dragging elements.

To use the application:

1. Clone the repository.
2. Install Python (version 3.9 or higher).
3. Install PostgreSQL (version 13 or higher).
4. Install the required packages by running the command: `pip install -r requirements.txt`.
5. Set your database settings in the file: `employeeTree/employeeTree/settings.py`.
6. Migrate the database using the command: `python manage.py migrate`.
7. Create a superuser using the command: `python manage.py createsuperuser`.
8. Seed the database with employees using the command: `python manage.py seed --hierarchy-levels=7 --min-employees=50000`.
9. Run the development server with the command: `python manage.py runserver`.
10. Open your browser and navigate to [http://localhost:8000].
11. Enjoy exploring the Employee Tree application!